http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/%E2%80%9CComplete-UGD-work-quickly%E2%80%9D/article13989839.ece

The Communist Party of India (Marxist) has urged the municipal authorities to expeditiously complete underground drainage (UGD) work in Nagercoil.Condemning the undue delay in the UGD work, the cadres of the CPI (M) staged a demonstration in front of Sir C.V. Ramasamy Iyer Memorial Park at Veppamudu junction here on Friday, raising slogans against the municipality.Addressing the demonstrators, party area secretary Meenakshi Sundaram urged the local body to speed up the UGD work and relay the roads dug up for the project on a war footing. S. Noor Mohemed, State executive committee member, inaugurated the demonstration. District committee members S. Antony and Sagaya Antony, among others spoke.MDMK demoCadres of Marumalarchi Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam staged a demonstration in front of the Collectorate, pressing for the same demand.